- **HTTP `/-/reload`** — `case rc := <-webHandler.Reload():` (line 1308). Route registered in `/app/web/web.go` lines 567-568 (`router.Post/Put("/-/reload", h.reload)`); the handler `h.reload` (web.go line 934) sends a `chan error` into `h.reloadCh` (web.go line 937) and blocks on the reply. `Handler.Reload()` (web.go line 685) exposes `h.reloadCh`. On error, `rc <- err` propagates the failure back to the HTTP caller (returns HTTP 500).
